    <p>Last year, Sin­ga­pore threw out 744 mil­lion kg of food</p>
    <p>– the weight of about 51,000 dou­ble-decker buses.</p>
    <p>For a na­tion which loves food so much, why does so much of it end up in the bin? The Sun­day Times polled 1,000 Sin­ga­pore­ans and per­ma­nent res­i­dents to find out what peo­ple here think and do when it comes to food.</p>
    <p>Here are some key find­ings.</p>

